Rates for each reaction channel r_i calculated from current state.\n        2. The timestep tau is chosen randomly from an exponential distribution P ~ e^(-W tau).\n        3.  1866:     """
 1867:     Susceptible, Exposed, Asymptomatic and infected, Infected, Removed, Quarantined (SEAIRQ)
 1868: 
 1869:     * Ia: asymptomatic
 1870:     * Is: symptomatic
 1871:     * E: exposed
 1872:     * A: asymptomatic and infectious
 1873:     * Q: quarantined
 1874: 
 1875:     ...
 1876: 
 1877:     Parameters
 1878:     ----------
 1879:     parameters: dict
 1880:         Contains the following keys:
 1881: 
 1882:         alpha: float, np.array(M,)
 1883:             fraction of infected who are asymptomatic.
 1884:         beta: float
 1885:             rate of spread of infection.
 1886:         gIa: float
 1887:             rate of removal from asymptomatic individuals.
 1888:         gIs: float
 1889:             rate of removal from symptomatic individuals.
 1890:         gE: float
 1891:             rate of removal from exposed individuals.
 1892:         gA: float
 1893:             rate of removal from activated individuals.
 1894:         fsa: float
 1895:             fraction by which symptomatic individuals self isolate.
 1896:         tE  : float
 1897:             testing rate and contact tracing of exposeds
 1898:         tA  : float
 1899:             testing rate and contact tracing of activateds
 1900:         tIa: float
 1901:             testing rate and contact tracing of asymptomatics
 1902:         tIs: float
 1903:             testing rate and contact tracing of symptomatics
 1904:         seed: long
 1905:             seed for pseudo-random number generator (optional).
 1906:     M: int
 1907:         Number of compartments of individual for each class.
 1908:         I.e len(contactMatrix)
 1909:     Ni: np.array(6*M, )
 1910:         Initial number in each compartment and class
 1911:     """

 3622:     The infected class has 5 groups:
 3623:     * Ia: asymptomatic
 3624:     * Is: symptomatic
 3625:     * Ih: hospitalized
 3626:     * Ic: ICU
 3627:     * Im: Mortality
 3628:     ...
 3629:     Parameters
 3630:     ----------
 3631:     parameters: dict
 3632:         Contains the following keys:
 3633:         alpha: float, np.array (M,)
 3634:             fraction of infected who are asymptomatic.
 3635:         beta: float
 3636:             rate of spread of infection.
 3637:         gIa: float
 3638:             rate of removal from asymptomatic individuals.
 3639:         gIs: float
 3640:             rate of removal from symptomatic individuals.
 3641:         fsa: float
 3642:             fraction by which symptomatic individuals self isolate.
 3643:         gE: float
 3644:             rate of removal from exposeds individuals.
 3645:         gA: float
 3646:             rate of removal from activated individuals.
 3647:         gIh: float
 3648:             rate of hospitalisation of infected individuals.
 3649:         gIc: float
 3650:             rate hospitalised individuals are moved to intensive care.
 3651:         seed: long
 3652:             seed for pseudo-random number generator (optional).
 3653:     M: int
 3654:         Number of compartments of individual for each class.
 3655:         I.e len(contactMatrix)
 3656:     Ni: np.array(9*M, )
 3657:         Initial number in each compartment and class.
